Center: OECD/NEA Nuclear Data Bank, Boulogne-Billancourt, France
title: -High Resolution Neutron Capture and Total Cross Section Measurements of Cr-50, Cr-52 and Cr-53.

x4codes.hlp: SCK CEN (Belgian Nuclear Research Centre), Mol, Belgium

x4freetext: -HIGH RESOLUTION NEUTRON CAPTURE AND TOTAL CROSS
SECTION MEASUREMENTS OF CR-50, CR-52 AND CR-53.
GEEL 150 MEV LINAC, GELINA. OPERATED AT
4.5 NS BURST WIDTH AND 800 HZ REPETITION RATE.
.ENRICHED SAMPLES IN THE FORM OF OXIDE PWDERS WERE
USED. THEY WERE CANNED IN THIN ALUMINIUM CONTAINERS
OF EITHER 8 CM OR 3.5 CM DIAMETER. COMPOSITION AS
.CAPTURE EXPERIMENTS, THE FLIGHT PATH WAS 58.0 M.
FOR THE CAPTURE MEASUREMENTS THE SAMPLES
WERE VIEWED BY A PAIR OF C6D6 LIQUID SCINTILLATORS
OF 10.2 CM DIAMETER AND 7.6 CM HEIGHT, PLACED WITH
THEIR AXES PERPENDICULAR TO THE NEUTRON BEAM.
.FOR THE TRANSMISSION MEASUREMENTS AT 48.9 M, TWO
DETECTORS AND ONE 10-B4C DETECTOR WAS USED.
AT THE OTHER TWO FLIGHT PATHS, A 2.5 CM THICK NE110
SINGLE LEVEL BREIT-WIGNER AREA ANALYSIS, AND
.THE DATA WERE CORRECTED FOR BACKGROUND AND FLUX
